Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statement_list
Rule 2     statement_list -> statement
Rule 3     statement_list -> statement_list statement
Rule 4     statement -> DP DOT IDENTIFIER LPAREN IDENTIFIER COMMA IDENTIFIER RPAREN
Rule 5     statement -> DP DOT IDENTIFIER LPAREN IDENTIFIER RPAREN
Rule 6     statement -> DP DOT IDENTIFIER LPAREN STRING RPAREN
Rule 7     statement -> DP DOT IDENTIFIER LPAREN IDENTIFIER COMMA STRING RPAREN
Rule 8     statement -> LOAD STRING AS IDENTIFIER
Rule 9     statement -> FILTER IDENTIFIER WHERE IDENTIFIER comparison NUMBER AS IDENTIFIER
Rule 10    statement -> PLOT IDENTIFIER AS IDENTIFIER
Rule 11    comparison -> GREATER
Rule 12    comparison -> LESS
Rule 13    comparison -> EQUALS

Terminals, with rules where they appear

AS                   : 8 9 10
COMMA                : 4 7
DOT                  : 4 5 6 7
DP                   : 4 5 6 7
EQUALS               : 13
FILTER               : 9
GREATER              : 11
IDENTIFIER           : 4 4 4 5 5 6 7 7 8 9 9 9 10 10
LESS                 : 12
LOAD                 : 8
LPAREN               : 4 5 6 7
NUMBER               : 9
PLOT                 : 10
RPAREN               : 4 5 6 7
STRING               : 6 7 8
WHERE                : 9
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

comparison           : 9
program              : 0
statement            : 2 3
statement_list       : 1 3

Parsing method: LALR

